Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> https://tenor.com/view/joker-laugh-smile-gif-15101538

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Removing the shite VRSC code from our codebase allows important internals things to be much easier, such as making binaries for our DragonHeads

Author: Gateway#3763

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Mike wrote code that only works on Intel hardware, and it horribly fails on other architectures and causes problems, like on ARMv8 (newer rpi's and friends) and aarch64 (rpi3 and older)

Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> SDL does not need to download the full blockchain, so it's very good for people that pay for bandwidth or have slow connections

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> I don't know exact calculations, but I would guess it uses tens of megabytes of bandwidth, versus over 1GB for a Hush full node to sync currently

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> so my rough estimate would be SDL maybe uses 10X-100X less bandwidth

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> you can also still connect the android app to SDL! The android app can connect to :SD: or SDL and I think that is pretty awesome
